# 3) What's the difference between and abolute and a relative path in your terminal?
    #An absolute path in the terminal refers to to the full path starting at the root and making the way up or down. It is not dependent on the current directory that the user is in. Relative path, however, is dependent on the current directory that one is in and it refers to a path relative to this current location (cd ..)
